<RESOLUTION><CATEGORY>Repeal</CATEGORY>
<CREATED>1781540512</CREATED>
<DESC><![CDATA[The Security Council,

Agreeing with the original intentions of the proposal as being a genuine attempt to thwart invading forces from capturing [region]Empires Forever United[/region] (henceforth known as EFU) and preventing it from falling into raider hands,

Reflecting that the &quot;reiterating&quot; clause, while true at the time of the target&#39;s Injunction, it has not been accurate for a long while,

Acknowledging that in the present day the resolution has become a significant impediment for the region and is detrimental to both its security and development,

Recognising that the Injunction has inadvertently damaged EFU&#146;s security as it has allowed the region to become a prime target for tag raids, something that many have sadly taken advantage of causing major disruptions to the regional government due to the lack of a stable World Assembly Delegate,

Realising that due to the region&#146;s unbalanced and fragile situation, it is more beneficial for the residents to be given the option to transition to a stronghold which will permanently secure it under native control,

Believing that Security Council resolution #524 has fulfilled its purpose a long time ago and has been long overdue for a repeal,

Hereby Repeals SC #524]]></DESC>
